    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const body = $json.body ?? $json;\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    photo_base64: body.photo_base64 || \"\",\n    name: body.name || \"\",\n    phone: body.phone || \"\",\n    email: body.email || \"\",\n    message: body.message || \"\",\n    credence_ref: body.credence_ref || \"\",\n    credence_name: body.credence_name || \"\",\n    credence_famille: body.credence_famille || \"\",\n    plan_ref: body.plan_ref || \"\",\n    plan_name: body.plan_name || \"\",\n    plan_famille: body.plan_famille || \"\",\n    facade_ref: body.facade_ref || \"\",\n    facade_name: body.facade_name || \"\",\n    facade_famille: body.facade_famille || \"\"\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-bbbb-000000000002",
      "name": "Parse Input",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [480, 460]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "chat",
        "operation": "message",
        "modelId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "gpt-4.1-mini",
          "mode": "id"
        },
        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "You are an expert in interior design prompt engineering specialized in photorealistic kitchen surface renovation using Cover Styl' adhesive films.\n\nYour role is to convert specific Cover Styl' product references into a precise image editing prompt.\n\nCORE RULES:\n- You must ONLY describe surface modifications\n- NEVER describe layout, structure, objects, lighting, or camera\n- ALL geometry, positions, and structure must remain strictly unchanged\n- Use the Cover Styl' reference information to describe EXACTLY what material/color/finish to apply\n\nFor each element, if the reference is empty or \"inchangé\", output \"inchangé\".\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT - exactly 3 lines):\nfaçade: [description based on Cover Styl' reference or \"inchangé\"]\ncrédence: [description based on Cover Styl' reference or \"inchangé\"]\nplan de travail: [description based on Cover Styl' reference or \"inchangé\"]\n\nEach description must be max 25 words, physically accurate, specifying: material, color, finish, texture pattern.",
              "role": "system"
            },
            {
              "content": "=Crédence: Reference {{ $json.credence_ref }} - {{ $json.credence_name }} (Famille: {{ $json.credence_famille }})\nPlan de travail: Reference {{ $json.plan_ref }} - {{ $json.plan_name }} (Famille: {{ $json.plan_famille }})\nFaçade: Reference {{ $json.facade_ref }} - {{ $json.facade_name }} (Famille: {{ $json.facade_famille }})\nMessage client: {{ $json.message }}",
              "role": "user"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "temperature": 0.3,
          "maxTokens": 300
        }
      },
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-bbbb-000000000003",
      "name": "GPT-4.1-mini - Generate Structured Prompt",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
      "typeVersion": 1.8,
      "position": [700, 460],
      "credentials": {
        "openAiApi": {
          "id": "kuPsvuQRCRnBhXx5",
          "name": "OpenAi account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const text = $json.message?.content || $json.text || $json.choices?.[0]?.message?.content || \"\";\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    style_rewritten: text.trim(),\n    photo_base64: $('Parse Input').first().json.photo_base64,\n    name: $('Parse Input').first().json.name,\n    phone: $('Parse Input').first().json.phone,\n    email: $('Parse Input').first().json.email,\n    message: $('Parse Input').first().json.message,\n    credence_ref: $('Parse Input').first().json.credence_ref,\n    credence_name: $('Parse Input').first().json.credence_name,\n    plan_ref: $('Parse Input').first().json.plan_ref,\n    plan_name: $('Parse Input').first().json.plan_name,\n    facade_ref: $('Parse Input').first().json.facade_ref,\n    facade_name: $('Parse Input').first().json.facade_name\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-bbbb-000000000004",
      "name": "Extract Rewritten Style",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [920, 460]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const b64 = $json.photo_base64;\n// Strip data URI prefix if present\nconst raw = b64.replace(/^data:image\\/\\w+;base64,/, '');\nconst buffer = Buffer.from(raw, 'base64');\nreturn [{\n  json: { ...$json },\n  binary: {\n    data: {\n      data: raw,\n      mimeType: 'image/jpeg',\n      fileName: 'photo_source.jpg'\n    },\n    source_photo: {\n      data: raw,\n      mimeType: 'image/jpeg',\n      fileName: 'photo_source.jpg'\n    }\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-bbbb-000000000005",
      "name": "Decode Base64 Photo",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1140, 460]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "image",
        "operation": "edit",
        "modelId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "gpt-image-1",
          "mode": "id"
        },
        "prompt": "=You are an expert AI kitchen renovation simulator for CoverSwap using Cover Styl' adhesive films.\n\nPROJECT TYPE: Cuisine (Kitchen)\n\nSTYLE INSTRUCTIONS FROM COVER STYL' REFERENCES:\n{{ $json.style_rewritten }}\n\nCRITICAL RULES — STRUCTURE PRESERVATION:\n1. CAMERA LOCK: The viewpoint, angle, lens distortion, and perspective must remain EXACTLY identical to the source photo. No rotation, no zoom, no shift.\n2. GEOMETRY LOCK: Every edge, corner, surface boundary, handle position, appliance location, sink, faucet, outlet, and fixture must stay EXACTLY in place — pixel-perfect alignment.\n3. LIGHTING CONSISTENCY: Maintain the same light sources, shadow directions, ambient color temperature, and specular highlights. Only the surface reflectance changes — not the lighting setup.\n4. OBJECTS UNTOUCHED: All appliances, utensils, decorations, plants, towels, and personal items must remain perfectly intact — same position, same appearance.\n5. SURFACE-ONLY CHANGES: You may ONLY change the material, color, texture, and finish of the specified kitchen surfaces (façade, crédence, plan de travail). Nothing else.\n6. Apply Cover Styl' adhesive film textures faithfully — these are real premium vinyl wraps with specific material properties. The film should look naturally applied to the existing surface geometry, following all curves, edges, and relief.\n7. PHOTOREALISM: The result must be indistinguishable from a real photograph. Maintain grain, depth of field, lens artifacts, and environmental reflections consistent with the original image.\n8. If a surface is marked as \"inchangé\", keep it EXACTLY as in the original photo — do not modify it at all.\n\nApply ONLY the surface changes described above. Output a single photorealistic image.",
        "inputType": "base64",
        "binaryPropertyName": "data",
        "options": {
          "size": "1024x1024",
          "quality": "high"
        }
      },
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-bbbb-000000000006",
      "name": "OpenAI Image Edit",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
      "typeVersion": 1.8,
      "position": [1360, 460],
      "credentials": {
        "openAiApi": {
          "id": "kuPsvuQRCRnBhXx5",
          "name": "OpenAi account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const binary = $binary.data;\nconst base64 = binary.data;\nconst mimeType = binary.mimeType || 'image/png';\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    image_base64: `data:${mimeType};base64,${base64}`,\n    success: true\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1111-4aaa-bbbb-000000000007",
      "name": "Convert to Base64",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
